# Java Loops Programs

This folder contains Java programs that demonstrate the use of looping statements. Loops allow a block of code to execute repeatedly until a specified condition is met.

## 📚 Topics Covered

- For Loop
- While Loop
- Do-While Loop
- Nested Loops
- Loop Control Statements (break and continue)

## 📁 Programs Included

| No. | Program Name | Description |
|-----|--------------|-------------|
| 1 | PrintNumbers.java | Prints numbers from 1 to N. |
| 2 | SumOfNumbers.java | Finds the sum of the first N natural numbers. |
| 3 | EvenOddNumbers.java | Prints even and odd numbers from 1 to N. |
| 4 | MultiplicationTable.java | Displays the multiplication table of a given number. |
| 5 | Factorial.java | Calculates the factorial of a given number. |
| 6 | FibonacciSeries.java | Prints the Fibonacci series up to N terms. |
| 7 | PrimeNumber.java | Checks whether a number is prime. |
| 8 | ReverseNumber.java | Reverses the digits of a number. |
| 9 | PalindromeNumber.java | Checks whether a number is a palindrome. |
| 10 | ArmstrongNumber.java | Checks whether a number is an Armstrong number. |
| 11 | PerfectNumber.java | Checks whether a number is a perfect number. |
| 12 | StrongNumber.java | Checks whether a number is a strong number. |
| 13 | GCD.java | Finds the Greatest Common Divisor (GCD) of two numbers. |
| 14 | LCM.java | Finds the Least Common Multiple (LCM) of two numbers. |
| 15 | CountDigits.java | Counts the number of digits in a given number. |
| 16 | PatternPrinting.java | Prints various star and number patterns using nested loops. |

## 🎯 Learning Objectives

After completing these programs, you will be able to:

- Understand loop execution in Java.
- Use `for`, `while`, and `do-while` loops effectively.
- Solve mathematical problems using loops.
- Implement nested loops for pattern printing.
- Improve logical thinking and problem-solving skills.

## ▶️ How to Run

1. Open the program in your Java IDE or editor.
2. Compile the program:

```bash
javac FileName.java
```

3. Run the program:

```bash
java FileName
```

Example:

```bash
javac Factorial.java
java Factorial
```

## 🛠️ Technologies Used

- Java
- JDK 8 or above
- Scanner Class (`java.util.Scanner`)

